\begin_layout Plain Layout
The STM lithography is performed on SOI substrates which contain localization
 markers and preimplanted electrical contacts.
 These substrates are prepared in a cleanroom enviroment, processed on a
 wafer scale, bonded to a protective silicon cap and finally diced.
 The substrate is processed to have 2x1 reconstruction and is H terminated.
