\begin_layout Standard
Perform STM lithography on the SOI samples imposes high requirements for
 the sample surface quality.
 In particular, the atomic terrace width should be reasonably large (at
 least 10s of nanometers), the surface should have a 2x1 reconstruction
 with low defect concentration, the surface should be hydrogen terminated
 with low concentration of dangling bonds and the concentration of contaminants
 should be low.
 In the past, SOI substrates have been developed at CEA with sufficient
 surface quality.
 
\end_layout

